{"content": "Given:\n\n\\[\nf(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x\n\\]\n\\[\nf(5) = 3\n\\]\n\nWe are to find \\( f(-5) \\).\n\nFirst, let's compute \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a(-5)^3 + c(-5)\n\\]\n\nCalculate powers:\n\n- \\( (-5)^7 = -(5^7) \\)\n- \\( (-5)^3 = -125 \\)\n- \\( c(-5) = -5c \\)\n\nSo,\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = -(5^7) + a(-125) - 5c\n\\]\n\\[\n= -5^7 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\nNow, let's write \\( f(5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 5^7 + 125a + 5c = 3\n\\]\n\nNow, add \\( f(5) \\) and \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(-5) + f(5) = (-5^7 - 125a - 5c) + (5^7 + 125a + 5c)\n\\]\n\nThe like terms cancel:\n\n\\[\n= (-5^7 + 5^7) + (-125a + 125a) + (-5c + 5c)\n\\]\n\\[\n=", "in": 51, "out": 300}